section.section:
The board and its individual members are fiduciaries and shall act:
in good faith;
in a manner that is reasonably believed to be in the best interests of the corporation and its controlled affiliates or subsidiaries that offer health benefit plans;
in a manner that is reasonably believed to be in furtherance of the mission of the corporation as a nonprofit health service plan as required under § 14-102(c) of this subtitle; and
with the care that an ordinarily prudent person in a like position would use under similar circumstances.

The principal functions of the board shall include:
ensuring that the corporation effectively carries out the nonprofit mission established under § 14-102(c) of this subtitle;
selecting corporate management and evaluating its performance;
ensuring to the extent practicable that human resources and other resources are sufficient to meet corporate objectives;
subject to the provisions of subsection (d) of this section, nominating and selecting suitable candidates for the board;
establishing a system of governance at the board level, including an annual evaluation of board performance; and
before considering any bid or offer to acquire the nonprofit health service plan and to convert to a for-profit entity under Title 6.5 of the State Government Article, ensuring that adequate consideration is given to an independent valuation of the nonprofit health service plan.

The board shall have the following standing committees whose duties shall include:
an audit committee responsible for ensuring financial accountability;
a finance committee responsible for reviewing and making recommendations on the annual budget and for developing and recommending long-range financial objectives;
a compensation committee responsible for developing proposed compensation guidelines in accordance with § 14-139(d) of this subtitle;
a nominating committee responsible for identifying, evaluating, and recommending to the board individuals qualified to become board members, including individuals who represent a corporation for which the nonprofit health service plan is the sole member;
a service and quality oversight committee responsible for ensuring that policies and processes are in effect to assess and improve the quality of health insurance products provided to subscribers and certificate holders;
a mission oversight committee responsible for ensuring that the officers of the corporation act in accordance with the mission of the nonprofit health service plan;
a strategic planning committee responsible for examining long-range planning objectives, assessing strategies that may be used to implement the planning objectives, and analyzing the nonprofit health service plan's role in the insurance marketplace; and
any other committee that the board determines is necessary to carry out its duties.

The board shall approve in advance any action by the nonprofit health service plan, a corporation for which the plan is the sole member, or any affiliate or subsidiary of the nonprofit health service plan to:
materially modify options available in benefit plans marketed in the State;
materially modify Maryland provider networks or Maryland provider reimbursement levels;
materially modify underwriting guidelines for products marketed in the State;
materially modify rates or rating plans that are required to be approved by the Commissioner;
add a product to or withdraw a product from the Maryland market, withdraw from a line or type of business in the State, or withdraw from a geographic region in the State;
materially modify marketing goals and objectives in the State; or
materially impact the availability or affordability of health care in the State.

A person may not be a member of the board if the person:
has defaulted on the payment of a monetary obligation to the nonprofit health service plan;
has been convicted of a criminal offense involving dishonesty or breach of trust or a felony;
habitually has neglected to pay debts; or
has been prohibited under any federal securities law from acting as a director or officer of any corporation.
